state "active\nprovider: AVAILABLE, STANDBY" as active
state "updating\nprovider: MAINTENANCE_IN_PROGRESS, PROVISIONING, RESTARTING, SCALE_IN_PROGRESS (+5 more)" as updating
state "failed\nprovider: repo-authored failure bucket" as failed
[*] --> provisioning : CreateAutonomousDatabase,\nUpdateAutonomousDatabase
provisioning --> active : AVAILABLE, STANDBY
active --> updating : ChangeAutonomousDatabaseCompartment,\nChangeAutonomousDatabaseSubscription\n(+8 more)
updating --> active : AVAILABLE, STANDBY
provisioning --> failed : unresolved OCI error or\nopen gap
updating --> failed : unresolved OCI error or\nopen gap
failed --> [*] : operator intervention
note right of active
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-controller-state-machine.svg
Start from the shared controller phase model and
specialize imported provider states, delete
targets, and failure exits here.
